ker_image\",\n      \"image\": \"neo4j:5.26-community\",\n      \"slug\": \"neo4j\",\n      \"reason\": \"The resolved artifact is the official Java access driver for Neo4j and its README's primary usage connects to a Bolt endpoint to run Cypher. The upstream driver test setup also uses Docker/Testkit/Testcontainers for integration coverage, so real driver behavior beyond value mapping requires a Neo4j server.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For tests that exercise GraphDatabase.driver, sessions, transactions, or executableQuery, start a Neo4j container, expose Bolt port 7687, set NEO4J_AUTH=neo4j/password, wait until verifyConnectivity or a simple query succeeds, and stop the container after tests. Pure Values/value-mapping tests do not need this setup.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The current reported java-run failure is in an in-process value-mapping test, so Docker is not necessarily needed to fix that specific assertion failure.\",\n    \"Docker-backed tests may be slower or flaky if startup readiness is not polled robustly.\",\n    \"Neo4j server compatibility should still be validated by the local Gradle and Native Image runs.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0bc956c593bf255d016a4211bc6f448197aaff6eaee5d36915\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 834, "output": 1024, "cacheRead": 34816, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36674, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782714801615, "responseId": "resp_0bc956c593bf255d016a4211b2108c8197b6ca24349c053e78"}, "toolResults": []}
